README: Quick Setup Guide for Client and Server

Install dependencies:

npm install
yarn install


Run the client:

npm run dev
yarn dev

2. Server (Spring Boot with MongoDB)
Prerequisites:

Java 17 or higher

MongoDB running locally or in the cloud
Configure MongoDB URI in application.properties:

spring.data.mongodb.uri=mongodb://localhost:27017/your-database

Run the server:
mvn clean install
mvn spring-boot:run

Server URL: http://localhost:8080

Now both the client and server are running!